ty (UK)|Socialist Equality Party]]: ''[https://web.archive.org/web/20100509015908/http://www.socialequality.org.uk/manifesto Socialist Equality Party Manifesto for the 2010 British General Election]''\n* [[Trade Unionist and Socialist Coalition]]: ''[http://www.tusc.org.uk/pdfs/TUSCmanifesto.pdf No To Cuts and Privatisation! Make the Bosses Pay!]''\n* [[Traditional Unionist Voice]]: ''[https://web.archive.org/web/20100602082522/http://www.tuv.org.uk/files/TUV-Manifesto.pdf Putting It Right]''\n* [[UK Independence Party]]: ''[http://www.ukip.org/media/pdf/UKIPManifesto2010.pdf Empowering the people]''\n* [[United Kingdom Libertarian Party]]: ''[https://web.archive.org/web/20090328001214/http://lpuk.org/pages/manifesto.php For Life, Liberty, and Prosperity]''\n\n=== Boundary Commissions ===\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20091028133311/http://www.boundarycommissionforengland.org.uk/ Boundary Commission for England]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100117094515/http://www.bcomm-scotland.gov.uk/index.html Boundary Commission for Scotland]\n* [http://www.bcomm-wales.gov.uk/ Boundary Commission for Wales]\n* [http://www.epolitix.com/EN/News/200606/2ff8ffa1-55a9-4907-a6f3-ea4467b2aaec.htm Boundary changes favour Tories] ePolitix, 26 June 2006\n\n{{Portal bar|Politics|United Kingdom}}\n{{2010 United Kingdom general election}}\n{{British elections}}\n{{Gordon Brown}}\n{{David Cameron}}\n{{Nick Clegg}}\n\n[[Category:2010 United Kingdom general election| ]]\n[[Category:General elections to the Parliament of the United Kingdom|2010]]\n[[Category:2010 elections in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:May 2010 events in the United Kingdom]]\n", "name_user": "Icantthinkofausernames", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExit poll", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2010_United_Kingdom_general_election"}
{"title_page": "B\u00e9atrice Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec", "text_new": "{{Infobox scientist\n| name              = B\u00e9atrice Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec\n| image             =\n| birth_place       = Lille, France\n| residence         = France\n| nationality       = French\n| fields            = Information & Communication Sciences, Communication Anthropology\n| workplaces        = Le Havre - Normandy University; UMR IDEES 6266 CNRS\n| alma_mater        = Paris V Sorbonne\n| thesis_title      = PhD in Sciences of Education\n| doctoral_advisor  = Gabriel Langou\u00ebt<!--(or  | doctoral_advisors = )-->\n| known_for         = Founded the Human-Trace and Sign-Trace Paradigms\n}}\n\nB\u00e9atrice Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec is emeritus professor in [[Communication Studies]], specialized in the fields of anthropology of communication and the analysis of the non-verbal dimension of interpersonal communication situations. Her approach to the interpretation of signs is based on the new wave of semiotics, known as [[anthroposemiotics]] where embodied semiotics takes a central position.\n\n== Biography ==\n\nProfessor Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec studied Economics at Toulouse<ref>B\u00e9atrice Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec et Julien P\u00e9quignot, \u00ab De l\u2019usage des traces en sciences de l\u2019information et de la communication \u00bb, Communiquer, n 27,\u200b 31 d\u00e9cembre 2019 (lire en ligne (http://journals.openedition.org/communiquer/4786 )). </ref>, obtaining a doctorate from the University of Paris V-Sorbonne [[University of Sorbonne]] in [[Education Sciences]] in 1988 under the supervision of the sociologist, Gabriel Langou\u00ebt. She was appointed as Associate Professor at the Institut des Sciences de l\u2019Information et de la Communication in 1989 at the University of Bordeaux-Montaigne [[University of Bordeaux]], and in 2002 became a University Professor of Information and Communication Sciences at [[University of Le Havre]], at Le Havre's Institute of Technology. \n\nAt [[Bordeaux]], she contributed to the launch in 1992, then to the development of the journal ''Communication & Organisation''<ref name=\"Author 2014\">{{cite web | last= | first= | title=1 - 1992 Communication et sentiment d'appartenance | website=OpenEdition Journals | date=1 November 2014 | url=http://journals.openedition.org/communicationorganisation/1341 | language=fr | access-date=22 December 2017}}</ref> . She set up the CDHET (Research Network for Communication and Human Development, Enterprises and Territories) <ref name=\"Welcome to nginx! 2012\">{{cite web | title=HISTORIQUE ET RAMIFICATIONS - CDHET (2016 \u00e0 \u2026) | website=Welcome to nginx! | date=6 February 2012 | url=http://litis.univ-lehavre.fr/labs/cdhet/wordpress/?page_id=9 | language=fr | access-date=22 December 2017}}</ref> , a research group which in 2000 opened up to interdisciplinary and inter-university research into the relationship between [[animal behavior]] and [[human behavior]]. Since 2008, she has been a permanent member of the joint research unit (UMR) of the [[Centre national de la recherche scientifique]]  CNRS-IDEES 6266 (National Centre for Scientific Research \u2013 Identities and Differentiation of the Environment of Spaces and Societies) at Normandie Universit\u00e9, where she supervises the Human Trace programme. \n \nIn 2011, she founded the International Research Group: Human Traces <ref name=\"umr-idees\">{{cite web |url=http://www.umr-idees.fr/?l-homme-trace |title=Laboratoire IDEES |website=UMR CNRS IDEES |language=fr}}</ref>. Since 2014, a network of researchers from various scientific backgrounds have been working on traces as part of the e. laboratory on Human Trace Complex System Digital Campus UNESCO which she founded RIGHT<ref name=\"Actualit\u00e9s 2011\">{{cite web | title=Actualit\u00e9s | date=21 July 2011 | url=https://rightunivlehavre.wordpress.com/actualites/ | language=fr | access-date=22 December 2017}}</ref> (the Research International Group: Human Traces). \n\nSince 2011, she has directed the Homme Trace series for CNRS \u00e9ditions. This is a collection of works regularly publishing articles by research scientists contributing to the emergence of \u201cThe new French school of thinking with respect to trace\u201d[1] (https://www.cnr seditions.fr/auteur/beatrice-galinon-melenec/)\n\n   \n== Research work ==\n\n=== Deconstruction of the term \"Trace\" ===\nB\u00e9atrice Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec denounces the simplification of the use of the notion of trace which, contrary to appearances, needs to be analysed in all its complexity. In her publications, she unveils the processes at work in human interpretation of the trace and, in line with the works of Jacques Derrida<ref>Derrida, Jacques., De la grammatologie, Les \u00c9ditions de Minuit, 1 janvier 1967 ({{ISBN|978-2-7073-0012-6}}, OCLC 906392252 (https://worldcat.org/oclc/906392252&lang=fr), lire en ligne (https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/906392252)) </ref>, encourages scientists who are concerned with epistemology<ref> GALINON-MELENEC B\u00e9atrice, \u00ab \u00c9pist\u00e9mologie de la notion de trace \u00bb, Pr\u00e9face de  ''L\u2019Homme-trace. Inscriptions corporelles et techniques'', Paris, CNRS \u00e9ditions, s\u00e9rie L\u2019Homme trace, tome 3, 2015, pp 9-27.</ref> to proceed with a systematic ''d\u00e9construction'' of the term<ref> \"la fabrique de la trace\" dans la conclusion de B\u00e9atrice Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec, in\u00ab \u00c0 la recherche de la trace \u00bb, ''Communication et organisation'' n\u00b0 47, 2015.http://journals.openedition.org/communicationorganisation/4876  </ref>.\n<ref>Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec B\u00e9atrice, ''L'Odyss\u00e9e de la trace 1. Voyage au-del\u00e0 des apparences,'' London, ISTE Editions, 2020 </ref>\n\n=== Sign-Trace. Semiotic embodied. Anthropo-semiotic. Relational semiotic ===\nWith the observation that everything that is potentially visible cannot necessarily be seen, B\u00e9atrice Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec starts from the hypothesis that signs only appear to individuals who are predisposed to receive them; this depends on their \"body-traces\"<ref>B\u00e9atrice Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec, L'Homme-Trace : Des traces du corps au corps-trace, Paris, CNRS Editions, 2017, 415 p. ({{ISBN|978-2-271-11417-4}}), quatri\u00e8me de couverture  </ref>, i.e. a body in which is recorded every consequence of the individual\u2019s interactions with the environments he/she has passed through over time. For the author, a human being\u2019s body-trace, (there is no separation between the body and the mind) possesses a plasticity which is the result of the interactions with the surroundings in which he/she lives (nature, culture, techniques, society, etc.)<ref> B\u00e9atrice Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec,  ''\"Homme-trace \u00bb et \u00ab signes-traces \u00bb, deux paradigmes fran\u00e7ais \u00e0 l\u2019\u00e9preuve des faits.'' Handicap psychique et recrutement, tome 2, Rouen, Klog Editions, 2012, 125 p. (ISBN 978-2-9539459-7-3)</ref>. \n\nThe interactions of a body with its surroundings being specific to each individual, the resulting body-trace is recorded in a difference, which modulates the reception of what is perceptible. To signify that the perception and interpretation of the sign are the consequences, the author suggests the term \"sign-trace\"<ref>B\u00e9atrice Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec, L'Homme-Trace : Des traces du corps au corps-trace, Paris, CNRS Editions, 2017, 415 p. ({{ISBN|978-2-271-11417-4}}), p. 10 </ref>.\n \nThis definition has been used by researchers and professionals to analyse situations of interpersonal communication where the body is present<ref>GALINON MELENEC B\u00e9atrice, MONSEIGNE Annick,, \u00ab \"La s\u00e9miotique des 'signes-traces' appliqu\u00e9e au recrutement : Le cas de la recherche du 'bon candidat' via les traces num\u00e9riques\" , \u00bb, ''Communication & organisation'', n\u00b0 39,,\u200e juin 2011, pp. 111-124. (lire en ligne [archive])</ref>. In this context, the interpretation of sign emitted by bodies appears as if recorded in a systemic dynamic linking the body-trace of the interpreted and the body-trace of the interpetant within a complex where bodies in co-presence are moved by permanent interactions of traces<ref>B\u00e9atrice Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec, L'Homme-Trace : Des traces du corps au corps-trace, Paris, CNRS Editions, 2017, 415 p. ({{ISBN|978-2-271-11417-4}}), quatri\u00e8me de couverture </ref>. \n\nThis approach finds its applications in various domains \u2013 internal business communication, recruitment<ref>Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec, B\u00e9atrice, ed. (2011). L'Homme Trace - Perspectives Anthropologiques des Traces Contemporaines (in French). CNRS Editions. {{ISBN|978-2271-07139-2}}.</ref>, doctor-patient relationships<ref>GALINON-MELENEC B\u00e9atrice, \u00ab Du diagnostic m\u00e9dical au diagnostic social, le signe-trace au fil des jours \u00bb', dans Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec B. (dir.), ''L'Homme trace, Perspectives anthropologiques des traces contemporaines'', Paris, CNRS \u00e9ditions, 2011, pp. 171-191.</ref> \u2013 and puts into perspective the biaises introduced by remote communication.\n\n=== Ichnos-Anthropos (Human-Trace) ===\nThe human being is a \"human trace\" (Ichnos-Anthropos) whose body traces carry the \u201cconsequence-trace\u201d interactions of inside-outside dualism. According to the author, body-trace and environment-trace have been retroacting in a systemic dynamic since the beginning of humanity, which explains the co-evolution of species and the environment<ref>Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec B\u00e9atrice,, \u00ab Pour une ichnologie g\u00e9n\u00e9rale \u00e0 l\u2019heure du num\u00e9rique \u00bb, 2020. \u00bb, Communication et traces num\u00e9riques, n\u00b01,Presses universitaires du Havre et de Rouen, 2020</ref>\nThe interpretation that the Ichnos-Anthropos makes of the real comes from anthropo-semiotics, where signs appear as the result of an interaction between the body-trace of Ichnos-Anthropos and the reality-trace of the world. With the anthropological Human-Trace paradigm, B\u00e9atrice Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec sets the figurative stage of homo (sapiens or otherwise) from any era whose body carries traces (ichnos) of the past (his or those of humans who have preceded him) and whose present relationship with the world participates permanently in the production of a future integrating the \"consequence-traces\" of his present actions<ref>GALINON-MELENEC B\u00e9atrice,  \u00ab The future of the \"Homme-trace\", A substantial societal challenge \u00bb, ''NETCOM'', 28-1/2 (2014), pp. 107-130,  (publication en anglais),   http://netcom.revues.org/1554.</ref>. As they were spread and appropriated by others, the term \"Human-Trace\" lost the paradigmatic dimension initially sought by the author. The effect of this being a preference for the Greek translation of \"Ichnos-Anthropos\" for the instances when referring to it in the strict sense of the paradigm.\n\n=== Influence ===\n\nThere has been a growing interest in the terms \"human trace\", \"body-trace\" and \"sign-trace\"<ref>Pequinot Julien, \u00ab Entretien avec B\u00e9atrice Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec \u00bb, ''Communiquer'', \"revue de communication sociale et publique\",\u200e 2020, pp. 91-115 (ISSN 2368-9587)</ref>. Nevertheless, if reference is made to certain indexing tools [[Google Scholar]], the citations lead us to conclude that their uses in French articles in the humanities between 2008-2018 are more often linked to the evocative power of the words that form them than the systemic, dynamic and multi-scale perspective that they encompass for their author. \n\nThe traces of digital consultations of the works and publications reveal a 60% readership belonging to academia and from various geographical horizons <ref> Academia.edu </ref> (The United States, Canada, Brazil, The United Kingdom, Italy, Romania, Spain, Morocco, Tunisia, Senegal, South Korea, Japan, Indonesia, Thailand, India, The Philippines, Turkey, Mauritius, Burkina Faso, Cameroon, Gabon, Ivory Coast, Niger, Swiss).\n\nIn 2020, during the COVID-19 pandemic, observations of the consequence-traces of human confinement on the decrease in pollution <ref> (en) Nasa, \u00ab How the coronavirus is and is not affecting the environment\u00bbhttps://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/blogs/earthmatters/2020/03/05/how-the-coronavirus-is-and-is-not-affecting-the-environment/ [archive]</ref>, extends the author\u2019s influence which had repeatedly warned about the pragmatic interest of the [[ecosystem]] present in the Human-Trace paradigm. The modelling of the semiotic emergence of the  \"sign-trace\" via the \"body-trace\" \u2013 which highlights the specific relationship between a human-trace in constant evolution and a reality-trace constantly evolutionary \u2013 acts as a support to psychological, sociological, cognitive and ecological analysis of the observations<ref>Pequinot Julien, \u00ab Entretien avec B\u00e9atrice Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec \u00bb, Communiquer, \"revue de communication sociale et publique\",\u200b 2020, pp. 91-115 (ISSN 2368-9587 (http://worldcat.org/issn/2368-9587&lang=fr)) </ref>.\n\n== Main publications ==\n\n=== In French ===\n* ''L'Homme-Trace : Des traces du corps au corps-trace,'' Paris, CNRS Editions, 2017, 415 p. ({{ISBN|978-2-271-11417-4}}) \n* ''L'Odyss\u00e9e de la trace 1. Voyage au-del\u00e0 des apparences'', London, ISTE Editions, 2020.\n* \u00ab Homme-trace \u00bb et \u00ab signes-traces \u00bb, deux paradigmes fran\u00e7ais \u00e0 l\u2019\u00e9preuve des faits., Rouen, Klog Editions, 2012, 125 p. ({{ISBN|978-2-9539459-7-3}}) \n* ''L'homme trace : perspectives anthropologiques des traces contemporaines'', Paris, CNRS Editions, 2011, 410 p. ({{ISBN|978-2-271-07139-2}}) \n* ''Penser autrement la communication : Du sens commun vers le sens scienti\ufb01que. Du sens scienti\ufb01que vers la pratique'', Paris/Budapest/Kinshasa etc., L'Harmattan, 2007, 247 p.({{ISBN|978-2-296-02658-2}}) \n* ''Homme/animal : quelles relations ? Quelles communications ?'', Mont-Saint-Aignan, Presses Universitaires Rouen, 2003, 228 p.({{ISBN|2-87775-353-0}}) \n* ''De la formation \u00e0 l'emploi, le r\u00f4le de la communication'', Presses Universitaires Pau, 1994, 256 p. ({{ISBN|978-2-908930-15-3}}) \n* ''Projet et communication dans les universit\u00e9s'', Editions d'Organisation, 1991, 225 p. ({{ISBN|978-2-7081-1320-6}}) \n* Avec Sami Zlitni, ''Traces num\u00e9riques : De la production \u00e0 l'interpr\u00e9tation'', Paris, CNRS Editions, 2015, 290 p.(ISBN 978-2-271-07239-9) \n* Avec Fabien Lienard et Sami Zlitni, ''L'homme-trace : Inscriptions corporelles et techniques'', Paris, CNRS Editions, 2015, 284p. ({{ISBN|978-2-271-08324-1}}) \n* Avec Fabienne Martin-Juchat, ''Le corps communicant : le XXIe si\u00e8cle, civilisation du corps ?'', Paris, L'Harmattan, 2008, 239p. ({{ISBN|978-2-296-04597-2}})\n\n\n=== Online Articles ===\n* (en) \u00ab From Traces and Human Trace to Human-Trace Paradigm \u00bb, Springer Proceedings in Complexity,\u200b 2015, p. 337349 (lire en ligne (https://www.springer.com/us/book/9783319459004)) \n* \u00ab A la recherche de la trace \u00bb, ''Communication et Organisation,''\u200b 2015, p. 31-50 (lire en ligne (http://communicationorganisation.revu es.org/4876)) (en) \n* (en) \u00ab The future of the Homme-trace \u00bb, ''Netcom'',\u200b 2014, p. 107-130 (lire en ligne (http://netcom.revues.org/1554)) \n* Avec Fabienne Martin-Juchat, \u00ab Du \u00ab genre \u00bb social au \u00ab genre \u00bb incorpor\u00e9 : Le \u00ab corps genr\u00e9 \u00bb des SIC \u00bb, ''Revue fran\u00e7aise des sciences de l\u2019information et de la communication,''\u200b 2014.(lire en ligne (http://rfsic.revues.org/857)) \n* \u00ab Exp\u00e9rience incarn\u00e9e, construction cognitive et jugement \u00bb, ''Revue fran\u00e7aise des sciences de l\u2019information et de la communication'',\u200b 2013 (lire en ligne (http://rfsic.revues.org/487)) \n* \u00ab Des signes-traces \u00e0 l\u2019Homme-trace. La production et l\u2019interpr\u00e9tation des traces plac\u00e9es dans une perspective anthropologique \u00bb, ''Intellectica,''\u200b 2013 (lire en ligne (http://intellectica.org/fr/des-signes-traces-l-homme-trace-la-production-et-l-interpretation-d es-traces-placees-dans-une perspective anthropoloogique))\n\n== Notes and references ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External Links ==\n* Notices d'autorit\u00e9 : Fichier d\u2019autorit\u00e9 international virtuel (http://viaf.org/viaf/22192278) \u00b7 International Standard Name Identi\ufb01er (http://isni.org/isni/0000000078316073)\u00b7 Biblioth\u00e8que nationale de France (http://catalogue.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/cb12219118h) (donn\u00e9es (http://data.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/cb12219118h.Syst\u00e8me universitaire de documentation (http://www.idref.fr/030860075). Biblioth\u00e8que du Congr\u00e8s(http://id.loc.gov/authorities/n93048180) Gemeinsame Normdatei (http://d-nb.info/gnd/1147774366) \u00b7 Biblioth\u00e8que nationale tch\u00e8que (http://aut.nkp.cz/vse2005290992).https://www.bookdepository.com/Whos-Who-World-Marquis-Whos-Who/9780837911298. https://www.whoswho.fr/bio/beatrice-galinon-melenec_79549. WorldCat (http://www.worldcat.org/identities/lccn-n93-048180) \n* Video on the ''CS-DC\u201915 \ufb01rst world conference'' (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k0A46_Vki6s) Galinon-Melenec B\u00e9atrice, The Explosion of questions posed by the traces: an answer in the paradigm of the HumanTrace (Arizona, USA, 2015) \n* Compte rendu  par Philippe Boissinot de : Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec B, \"L'Homme-trace\", tome I, 2011dans ''la revue Annales. Histoire, Sciences sociales'', 70e ann\u00e9e, no 2, avril-juin 2015, p. 543-545, 2015 (https://muse.jhu.edu/article/600762/pdf)\n* Compte rendu par Annick Monseigne de \u00ab B\u00e9atrice Galinon-M\u00e9l\u00e9nec (dir.), \"L\u2019Homme trace : perspectives anthropologiques des traces contemporaines \u00bb, 